WEBVTT

00:00:00.344 --> 00:00:01.944
(Child actors were accompanied by a guardian...)

00:00:01.944 --> 00:00:03.584
(and filmed in a safe, supervised environment.)

00:00:06.454 --> 00:00:09.184
- The person is unavailable... - This is driving me crazy.

00:00:09.684 --> 00:00:10.684
What do we do?

00:00:11.951 --> 00:00:13.451
- The person is unavailable... - Seriously.

00:00:13.724 --> 00:00:16.094
Why won't Bucket answer his phone?

00:00:16.624 --> 00:00:18.094
I'm going to wring his neck.

00:00:18.894 --> 00:00:20.764
- Dad. - Just leave him be.

00:00:22.334 --> 00:00:24.434
What if they get into another fight?

00:00:24.564 --> 00:00:27.334
If he has reason to fight, let him. Why must he always just take it?

00:00:28.004 --> 00:00:29.574
Let's just grill the meat and eat.

00:00:29.844 --> 00:00:32.874
- What? - Leave him be. The food's ready.

00:00:32.944 --> 00:00:33.944
Just eat.

00:00:35.514 --> 00:00:38.214
Uncle. Are you sure you're okay with not moving?

00:00:38.614 --> 00:00:39.854
Dong Suk said she's opening a shop.

00:00:40.514 --> 00:00:42.484
So it's not like I'll have to see her every day.

00:00:43.084 --> 00:00:44.624
But you're in the same neighborhood.

00:00:44.624 --> 00:00:46.624
What if your stomach hurts every time you run into her?

00:00:47.854 --> 00:00:48.924
Hey.

00:00:49.364 --> 00:00:50.894
But the funny thing is,

00:00:51.364 --> 00:00:53.064
maybe it's because I thought I was moving.

00:00:53.634 --> 00:00:55.334
My stomach didn't hurt even when we slept together.

00:00:56.034 --> 00:00:58.004
- What did you just say? - What did I say?

00:00:58.074 --> 00:01:00.004
"My stomach didn't hurt even when we slept together."

00:01:00.804 --> 00:01:01.804
I did?

00:01:02.544 --> 00:01:05.044
Woo Jae, why is your mind always in the gutter?

00:01:05.114 --> 00:01:06.644
Not "slept together." I meant...

00:01:07.914 --> 00:01:09.044
Even when I saw her.

00:01:10.414 --> 00:01:15.024
- "Saw her?" - Yes, I meant even when I saw her.

00:01:17.254 --> 00:01:21.394
So, Dad, you weren't helping me open a shop for my sake.

00:01:21.664 --> 00:01:24.264
It was all just a ploy so he could get on "Human Theater."

00:01:24.264 --> 00:01:25.334
The person you're calling is unavailable...

00:01:26.064 --> 00:01:29.704
Dad. If their family moves, will you still help me get a shop?

00:01:30.634 --> 00:01:32.534
I always keep my word.

00:01:33.634 --> 00:01:35.274
- You heard him, right? - Yes.

00:01:35.374 --> 00:01:36.844
Pick up, Se Ri. Please, just pick up.

00:01:37.474 --> 00:01:39.674
Why isn't she answering?

00:01:40.414 --> 00:01:42.614
But how did that letter end up with our stepmom?

00:01:42.884 --> 00:01:43.914
Dad, you gave it to her?

00:01:43.914 --> 00:01:45.254
- The person you're calling... - I did.

00:01:45.754 --> 00:01:48.824
- But I gave it to Seong Mi. - That explains it.

00:01:49.084 --> 00:01:51.354
She must have passed it on to her.

00:01:51.754 --> 00:01:55.124
Seriously, Dad, why do you always have to complicate things?

00:01:55.524 --> 00:01:58.494
- This is all your fault, you brat. - How is this my fault?

00:01:58.564 --> 00:01:59.864
You're the one who told me to write the letter.

00:02:00.234 --> 00:02:02.064
You asked me to come up with a plan for you.

00:02:02.564 --> 00:02:03.764
See? What did I tell you?

00:02:04.164 --> 00:02:05.934
I told you to come clean before you got caught, didn't I?

00:02:06.904 --> 00:02:09.844
Aunt must have been really upset. To think she actually ran away.

00:02:10.074 --> 00:02:13.374
Of course. She managed family matters by herself,

00:02:13.744 --> 00:02:15.914
so to be completely left out of something this big...

00:02:16.484 --> 00:02:17.644
The sense of betrayal must be overwhelming.

00:02:18.954 --> 00:02:22.724
You don't think she's gone for good, do you?

00:02:23.124 --> 00:02:24.454
Go find her and bring her back. Now!

00:02:26.124 --> 00:02:27.894
I'm seriously going to lose my mind.

00:02:29.764 --> 00:02:33.534
Hey, Bucket! Why didn't you answer my call?

00:02:34.094 --> 00:02:35.104
What are you doing here?

00:02:35.164 --> 00:02:38.634
You jerk! You really have to ask? Why were you meeting with Seong Mi?

00:02:39.034 --> 00:02:42.474
Look, I'm not in my right mind right now, so just go.

00:02:43.204 --> 00:02:46.374
You jerk! Do I look like I'm in my right mind?

00:02:48.684 --> 00:02:49.814
Hey, but...

00:02:50.414 --> 00:02:52.454
I'm the one who gave Seong Mi that letter.

00:02:52.814 --> 00:02:54.784
- But why did it... - What, you jerk?

00:02:55.524 --> 00:02:58.994
- You gave the letter to Seong Mi? - Don't change the subject, jerk.

00:02:59.294 --> 00:03:00.894
I'm asking why it ended up with Se Ri!

00:03:00.954 --> 00:03:04.594
How should I know? You've got some nerve, blaming me.

00:03:04.664 --> 00:03:06.464
Dad, that's enough.

00:03:07.094 --> 00:03:08.664
Father, that's enough. All right?

00:03:09.004 --> 00:03:10.334
When did you get here? Move.

00:03:11.034 --> 00:03:14.434
Hey! Why did you meet my Seong Mi and spill everything?

00:03:14.974 --> 00:03:17.374
You didn't get your way, so you decided to burn it all down?

00:03:17.504 --> 00:03:18.774
You're the one who went back on your word!

00:03:19.144 --> 00:03:22.684
You were so fickle. I was trying to bring you to your senses!

00:03:22.814 --> 00:03:24.584
And how did that work out for you?

00:03:25.054 --> 00:03:27.054
You should've kept your mouth shut!

00:03:27.054 --> 00:03:29.654
You shouldn't have butted in and made such a mess of things.

00:03:29.784 --> 00:03:34.224
- Dad, please. I'm so sorry. - You're the one who backed out!

00:03:34.354 --> 00:03:38.764
- How can a person be so fickle? - So I can't change my mind?

00:03:39.164 --> 00:03:42.164
- That's it. I'm moving! - Fine, go.

00:03:42.234 --> 00:03:43.964
- That's right. I'm leaving. - Then go!

00:03:44.034 --> 00:03:45.034
I said, I'm leaving!

00:03:45.704 --> 00:03:47.604
- Let's go, Dad. All right? - Let's go, Dad.

00:03:47.604 --> 00:03:50.844
Hey, I'm moving out tomorrow so I never have to see you again.

00:03:50.904 --> 00:03:53.414
Fine, go then, you jerk! Leave tomorrow!

00:03:53.474 --> 00:03:56.214
- Nothing's been right since we met. - Stop it.

00:03:56.344 --> 00:03:57.344
Leave first thing tomorrow.

00:03:57.414 --> 00:04:01.284
The same goes for me, you jerk! You punk, what are you kicking?

00:04:01.354 --> 00:04:03.684
If you don't move, I'll throw you out myself.

00:04:03.984 --> 00:04:05.854
- Go, you jerk. Just go! - Dad.

00:04:05.924 --> 00:04:07.094
Please.

00:04:07.694 --> 00:04:10.294
- You rotten punk. Move tomorrow! - Let's go.

00:04:10.294 --> 00:04:11.964
Why, you little... I can't even...

00:04:12.734 --> 00:04:13.964
For crying out loud.

00:04:17.464 --> 00:04:19.434
What was all that about?

00:04:21.234 --> 00:04:23.144
Your stepmom is gone, Hyun Bin.

00:04:24.004 --> 00:04:25.014
What?

00:04:25.514 --> 00:04:26.814
Behind Se Ri's back,

00:04:27.674 --> 00:04:30.014
I tried to stop Jeong Han's family from moving, and she found out.

00:04:31.754 --> 00:04:33.414
What do you mean you tried to stop them?

00:04:34.354 --> 00:04:35.854
I was going to tell her tomorrow,

00:04:37.384 --> 00:04:38.524
but it looks like she already found out.

00:04:39.924 --> 00:04:40.954
Hold on a second.

00:04:44.364 --> 00:04:45.734
She's not picking up your calls either, right?

00:04:46.594 --> 00:04:47.894
The person you're trying to reach is unavailable...

00:04:48.904 --> 00:04:51.064
What about tracking her location?

00:04:51.464 --> 00:04:52.474
She turned it off.

00:04:53.634 --> 00:04:55.004
She turned everything off and just vanished.

00:04:57.744 --> 00:04:58.914
What am I supposed to do now?

00:04:59.614 --> 00:05:02.744
When you decided to do this, didn't you think this might happen?

00:05:04.114 --> 00:05:05.154
I didn't.

00:05:06.154 --> 00:05:09.654
I thought no matter what I did, Se Ri would always stay by my side.

00:05:10.524 --> 00:05:13.924
Who in the world sticks by someone no matter what they do?

00:05:13.994 --> 00:05:15.364
People get divorced over the smallest things,

00:05:15.724 --> 00:05:17.394
and parents even abandon their own kids these days.

00:05:18.024 --> 00:05:19.034
Am I...

00:05:19.734 --> 00:05:20.934
being abandoned again?

00:05:23.164 --> 00:05:24.464
What am I really going to do?

00:05:26.004 --> 00:05:27.304
You crazy fool.

00:05:28.674 --> 00:05:29.744
You darn fool.

00:05:29.944 --> 00:05:33.714
Dad, what are you doing? Seriously, how is this helping?

00:05:33.774 --> 00:05:37.244
No, I deserve this. I'm such a fool.

00:05:38.014 --> 00:05:41.654
- I'm a fool! - Dad, please stop!

00:05:44.284 --> 00:05:45.424
You crazy fool.

00:05:51.994 --> 00:05:54.894
- That Bucket guy, I swear... - Dad.

00:05:56.134 --> 00:05:59.104
Did you ask Mom out just to tell her you weren't moving?

00:05:59.334 --> 00:06:00.334
I did.

00:06:01.074 --> 00:06:03.874
Dad, seriously... What is wrong with you?

00:06:04.204 --> 00:06:05.674
That's enough, okay?

00:06:05.674 --> 00:06:08.214
Everyone's been yelling at me, and I'm at my wits' end.

00:06:08.314 --> 00:06:11.414
So you went to Dr. Yang's house to take it out on him?

00:06:11.684 --> 00:06:14.714
Take it out on him? I was angry because he deserved it.

00:06:15.124 --> 00:06:17.454
And you. Weren't you supposed to pick up lettuce?

00:06:17.684 --> 00:06:18.954
Why were you over there with that guy?

00:06:19.254 --> 00:06:21.994
And what's with this bouquet? What is this?

00:06:23.064 --> 00:06:24.494
This is...

00:06:24.864 --> 00:06:26.834
A junior colleague from work gave it to me.

00:06:27.134 --> 00:06:30.104
Director Yang just gave me a ride since we were heading the same way,

00:06:30.164 --> 00:06:32.034
and we just stopped to talk for a second.

00:06:32.504 --> 00:06:34.634
And he's the director. Why are you calling him "that guy?"

00:06:34.874 --> 00:06:36.904
He's your director, not mine.

00:06:37.474 --> 00:06:38.774
And back there,

00:06:39.074 --> 00:06:41.784
why did you apologize to that jerk, Bucket?

00:06:41.844 --> 00:06:44.914
So what, I should've taken your side and fought with Director Yang?

00:06:45.484 --> 00:06:48.524
Dad, seriously, what is your problem?

00:06:48.954 --> 00:06:52.024
Are you allergic to getting along with Mom or something?

00:06:52.194 --> 00:06:53.454
Allergic? Don't be ridiculous...

00:06:55.294 --> 00:06:58.194
That reminds me. Hey, Ju Ah. Gong Ju Ah.

00:06:58.594 --> 00:06:59.664
What now?

00:06:59.934 --> 00:07:02.434
You need to talk to Woo Jae.

00:07:03.504 --> 00:07:04.604
Woo Jae? What's wrong with him now?

00:07:12.144 --> 00:07:13.144
Well, look at you.

00:07:13.574 --> 00:07:15.684
Just go live in the lettuce fields. Why are you back already?

00:07:16.884 --> 00:07:18.284
Did you hear about all the drama at home?

00:07:18.954 --> 00:07:21.714
Did I hear about it? Dad grabbed Dr. Yang by the collar,

00:07:21.784 --> 00:07:22.984
and I was the one who had to drag him home.

00:07:23.254 --> 00:07:24.254
Seriously?

00:07:25.154 --> 00:07:28.724
What are we going to do? How's Mom? Did you talk to her?

00:07:28.894 --> 00:07:31.294
Forget about that. Dad told me something.

00:07:31.624 --> 00:07:32.664
Are you on medication?

00:07:34.364 --> 00:07:36.964
I can't believe Dad told you that now of all times.

00:07:37.404 --> 00:07:40.404
You should have told me if something like that was going on.

00:07:40.604 --> 00:07:42.574
Don't worry about it. It's nothing.

00:07:42.744 --> 00:07:44.144
Is this why you said you wanted...

00:07:44.144 --> 00:07:46.044
to take a break from studying and get a job?

00:07:47.114 --> 00:07:51.244
This is insane. If you quit too, Mom will lose it.

00:07:51.584 --> 00:07:54.284
Don't worry. I'm not like you.

00:07:54.814 --> 00:07:58.124
How are you any different? I had an anxiety disorder, too.

00:07:58.154 --> 00:07:59.194
Don't you remember?

00:07:59.294 --> 00:08:02.464
You didn't want to be a doctor. I'm like this because I do.

00:08:03.924 --> 00:08:04.924
Gong Woo Jae.

00:08:05.694 --> 00:08:09.564
Live the life you want, not the one Mom wants for you.

00:08:12.274 --> 00:08:13.274
Okay.

00:08:14.004 --> 00:08:15.744
Once Mom is doing a little better,

00:08:17.204 --> 00:08:18.514
I'll come clean about everything.

00:08:20.244 --> 00:08:21.244
Seriously...

00:08:28.154 --> 00:08:29.254
I'm home.

00:08:31.684 --> 00:08:34.694
- Hyun Bin! - Did you find Se Ri?

00:08:35.154 --> 00:08:37.964
No. She's not picking up, and her car is gone.

00:08:38.594 --> 00:08:39.634
What are we going to do?

00:08:40.364 --> 00:08:41.364
Father.

00:08:42.164 --> 00:08:43.864
I think I've been abandoned again.

00:08:44.964 --> 00:08:46.274
I think she's going to divorce me.

00:08:47.104 --> 00:08:48.574
Divorce? Over something like this?

00:08:49.104 --> 00:08:50.174
There's no way.

00:08:50.674 --> 00:08:54.014
What do you mean, "no way?" In her shoes, I'd want a divorce.

00:08:54.244 --> 00:08:57.544
I can understand Eun Bin acting out, but you let it happen, Grandfather.

00:08:57.744 --> 00:09:01.114
How could you just stand by and let it get this bad?

00:09:02.284 --> 00:09:05.424
If she'll get a divorce over this, then let her.

00:09:05.494 --> 00:09:08.564
If that's all we mean to her, good riddance!

00:09:08.624 --> 00:09:12.364
Hey, will you shut it? This was all your doing, wasn't it?

00:09:13.494 --> 00:09:14.864
I can't believe you.

00:09:16.334 --> 00:09:18.704
Anyway, all of you need to think about what you've done.

00:09:19.804 --> 00:09:23.474
Dr. Gong's family is moving as planned. Just know that.

00:09:24.404 --> 00:09:25.414
Dad.

00:09:28.414 --> 00:09:29.884
I can't deal with this.

00:09:31.314 --> 00:09:34.614
Dad, what if she really doesn't come back?

00:09:43.494 --> 00:09:45.934
Do you have any idea where she might have gone?

00:09:46.364 --> 00:09:47.564
A friend's place, maybe?

00:09:49.064 --> 00:09:50.664
She doesn't have any friends.

00:09:52.074 --> 00:09:53.734
She's not close with the other doctors' wives...

00:09:54.034 --> 00:09:55.574
And she's not the type to air our dirty laundry.

00:09:56.904 --> 00:10:00.674
She grew up in an orphanage, so she has no blood relatives.

00:10:02.944 --> 00:10:04.384
Her whole adult life,

00:10:05.284 --> 00:10:06.554
she worked at a salon,

00:10:06.554 --> 00:10:09.354
then got pushed into a pageant. That's where we met.

00:10:10.754 --> 00:10:12.394
No friends, no relatives,

00:10:13.194 --> 00:10:16.094
nowhere to go, and nothing to her name.

00:10:18.934 --> 00:10:23.304
I said a wedding was embarrassing, so we'd just register the marriage.

00:10:24.664 --> 00:10:27.104
I told her I didn't believe in love, so she should just raise the kids,

00:10:27.434 --> 00:10:30.604
take care of my father, and run the house.

00:10:32.174 --> 00:10:33.774
And even after all that, Se Ri still chose to be with me.

00:10:36.044 --> 00:10:39.414
What did I do to a woman like that? Hyun Bin, what have I done?

00:10:53.694 --> 00:10:56.934
Day one of our relationship, and it's already been a rough ride.

00:11:01.234 --> 00:11:05.414
- Yes, Director. - Come on, "Director?" We're dating.

00:11:05.874 --> 00:11:09.514
My gosh, what should I call you then?

00:11:10.514 --> 00:11:11.844
Just say, "Hyun Bin."

00:11:12.214 --> 00:11:15.454
- I can't. - "Mr. Hyun Bin," then?

00:11:15.984 --> 00:11:16.984
No, I can't.

00:11:17.524 --> 00:11:20.154
- Yes, you can. - No, I can't.

00:11:20.694 --> 00:11:24.494
I'm worried it'll become a habit. What if I say it in front of others?

00:11:25.064 --> 00:11:26.164
All right.

00:11:26.994 --> 00:11:30.134
Then we can discuss it later.

00:11:31.064 --> 00:11:34.704
By the way, has your mom come home yet?

00:11:35.844 --> 00:11:39.774
Not yet. By the way, is Dr. Han doing any better?

00:11:41.344 --> 00:11:43.484
She's locked her door and won't come out.

00:11:44.614 --> 00:11:45.614
Oh, dear.

00:11:46.614 --> 00:11:50.584
When your mother gets back, please tell her we're moving out.

00:11:50.854 --> 00:11:51.854
I will.

00:11:52.924 --> 00:11:56.864
Wow, our first day is really off to a rough start, isn't it?

00:11:57.394 --> 00:11:58.794
Tell me about it.

00:12:00.564 --> 00:12:02.804
Hey, no sighing.

00:12:03.064 --> 00:12:05.704
Especially after we pinky-promised not to let things get to us.

00:12:06.774 --> 00:12:07.934
You're right.

00:12:09.074 --> 00:12:12.214
Man, hearing your voice really makes me miss you.

00:12:12.814 --> 00:12:14.044
Should I come over?

00:12:14.374 --> 00:12:16.784
Let's just see each other tomorrow. Tomorrow. Okay?

00:12:17.544 --> 00:12:18.884
Okay, I'll let you go then.

00:12:19.354 --> 00:12:21.284
See you tomorrow. Sleep well.

00:12:28.964 --> 00:12:29.964
What?

00:12:33.464 --> 00:12:34.934
Stepmother?

00:12:35.564 --> 00:12:37.164
You've been calling.

00:12:38.264 --> 00:12:39.434
I was driving.

00:12:40.074 --> 00:12:41.734
It would've been dangerous to answer.

00:12:41.974 --> 00:12:45.004
Right. I'm at my dad's house now. I heard everything.

00:12:45.174 --> 00:12:46.514
Where are you, by the way?

00:12:50.914 --> 00:12:51.984
On a little staycation.

00:12:52.754 --> 00:12:54.184
I just needed some time alone.

00:12:54.484 --> 00:12:58.224
I see. In that case, go wild with Grandfather's credit card,

00:12:58.384 --> 00:13:02.524
and get some good rest. I'll give them an earful for you.

00:13:03.164 --> 00:13:05.264
Okay. Thanks.

00:13:37.994 --> 00:13:39.034
Who's there?

00:13:39.994 --> 00:13:42.604
- Sister? - My gosh, Stella!

00:13:42.904 --> 00:13:44.004
Is that really you, Stella?

00:13:48.204 --> 00:13:52.974
It really is you. What brings you out here, especially at this hour?

00:13:53.674 --> 00:13:58.414
- Did I startle you by showing up? - No, it's great to see you.

00:13:58.914 --> 00:14:01.514
I've actually been thinking about you a lot lately.

00:14:02.054 --> 00:14:05.654
The Lord knew what was in my heart and guided you here.

00:14:07.324 --> 00:14:08.894
I've missed you, Sister.

00:14:29.544 --> 00:14:33.214
- Mother. - Hey. Did you get some sleep?

00:14:34.184 --> 00:14:37.124
Gosh, did you wake up early to make this for me?

00:14:37.224 --> 00:14:38.254
What?

00:14:38.654 --> 00:14:41.154
No, I was just making it for myself.

00:14:42.094 --> 00:14:44.724
But you made far more than you could possibly eat alone, didn't you?

00:14:46.164 --> 00:14:47.194
Yes.

00:14:51.934 --> 00:14:55.974
Here, drink water first, then eat. Your throat must be parched.

00:15:04.984 --> 00:15:06.784
You didn't have dinner either, did you, Mother?

00:15:06.984 --> 00:15:10.584
Of course not. How could I eat when you are on a hunger strike?

00:15:10.654 --> 00:15:11.754
Do you think I'd have any appetite?

00:15:12.254 --> 00:15:14.994
We're both being punished for my good-for-nothing son.

00:15:15.964 --> 00:15:20.634
- How is any of this your fault? - I swear, I didn't know.

00:15:20.694 --> 00:15:22.064
I wasn't in on it.

00:15:22.804 --> 00:15:24.104
I know.

00:15:33.974 --> 00:15:35.014
What's wrong?

00:15:36.684 --> 00:15:38.544
Have you lost your appetite?

00:15:39.284 --> 00:15:40.354
No.

00:15:41.654 --> 00:15:43.454
I can't eat it. It just doesn't taste good.

00:15:43.854 --> 00:15:45.424
For crying out loud.

00:15:46.194 --> 00:15:48.454
Nobody in the world would ever believe it.

00:15:48.824 --> 00:15:52.394
That the esteemed Dr. Han Seong Mi insults her mother-in-law's cooking.

00:16:05.944 --> 00:16:07.244
You know something?

00:16:10.184 --> 00:16:12.584
Are you talking in your sleep, or are you talking to me?

00:16:13.484 --> 00:16:15.614
Se Ri kept trying to convince me.

00:16:17.084 --> 00:16:19.124
She begged me not to send you to study abroad.

00:16:20.654 --> 00:16:22.624
She said she'd raise you well herself.

00:16:24.124 --> 00:16:25.124
I know.

00:16:26.794 --> 00:16:28.864
That's the kind of woman she is.

00:16:32.604 --> 00:16:33.874
Just get some more sleep.

00:16:40.174 --> 00:16:42.114
Eun Bin, you're not asleep?

00:16:43.914 --> 00:16:46.984
Hyun Bin, our stepmom still hasn't come home.

00:16:47.554 --> 00:16:50.524
I've called her dozens of times and sent her countless texts.

00:16:50.584 --> 00:16:51.854
How could she do this to us?

00:16:52.254 --> 00:16:54.124
I bet she wouldn't do this if I were her own daughter.

00:16:55.254 --> 00:16:58.464
A real daughter wouldn't make trouble like you do.

00:16:59.034 --> 00:17:02.634
You don't think Dad will divorce her because of me, do you?

00:17:02.904 --> 00:17:05.734
Goodness. You should've treated her better.

00:17:06.434 --> 00:17:08.104
Is Grandpa still asleep?

00:17:09.004 --> 00:17:11.474
- He left a while ago. - He left?

00:17:27.724 --> 00:17:30.624
Hey! I told you I'd handle it. What is with you, seriously?

00:17:30.694 --> 00:17:33.134
- Go on, go. - Hold on. Hey, what the...

00:17:33.194 --> 00:17:36.564
Listen, the second you walk in, you get down on your knees. Got it?

00:17:36.964 --> 00:17:39.774
Get on my knees? What for? Was what I did really that bad?

00:17:39.774 --> 00:17:43.044
- Yes, you messed up badly. Knock. - Hey, but...

00:17:45.504 --> 00:17:46.944
This is ridiculous.

00:17:51.914 --> 00:17:54.354
Hey, Seong Mi! Han Seong Mi!

00:17:54.784 --> 00:17:55.984
Honestly... Give me a break.

00:17:56.254 --> 00:18:00.754
- Gently. Be sweet. - Seriously. This is nuts.

00:18:05.864 --> 00:18:10.704
- Seong Mi. Are you awake? - Gosh, just open it. Hurry up.

00:18:11.064 --> 00:18:13.034
- What if it's locked? - Dad, come on...

00:18:13.104 --> 00:18:14.404
- Dad! - Please!

00:18:21.844 --> 00:18:24.314
- It's unlocked. Yes. - It is?

00:18:24.814 --> 00:18:26.414
- So, you go in. - What?

00:18:26.684 --> 00:18:28.384
Get on your knees, quick!

00:18:33.354 --> 00:18:34.554
Seong Mi.

00:18:35.494 --> 00:18:38.394
I really messed up this time. All right?

00:18:38.664 --> 00:18:42.464
Please, just let it slide this once. Seong Mi, I'm serious.

00:18:43.304 --> 00:18:44.364
Please...

00:18:44.704 --> 00:18:46.834
Seong Mi.

00:18:47.774 --> 00:18:48.774
What?

00:18:49.274 --> 00:18:51.774
Seong Mi!

00:18:52.774 --> 00:18:53.774
What?

00:18:56.944 --> 00:18:58.444
So, is Mom not coming out?

00:18:59.714 --> 00:19:01.854
She's gone.

00:19:04.154 --> 00:19:06.124
Wait, don't tell me... She ran away from home?

00:19:06.194 --> 00:19:09.024
Hey! Don't be ridiculous. She didn't run away!

00:19:09.094 --> 00:19:12.494
This is why you should've apologized last night.

00:19:12.634 --> 00:19:15.064
She locked the door and wouldn't answer,

00:19:15.064 --> 00:19:17.504
no matter how many times I knocked. What was I supposed to do?

00:19:20.804 --> 00:19:22.904
Grandma's not here either.

00:19:23.174 --> 00:19:24.574
What?

00:20:01.274 --> 00:20:04.884
So? It's better than the porridge you make, right?

00:20:05.714 --> 00:20:06.754
I suppose it is.

00:20:07.584 --> 00:20:09.454
I can't tell if it tastes good because someone else made it,

00:20:09.524 --> 00:20:12.694
or because we're eating by the sea for the first time in a while.

00:20:15.124 --> 00:20:18.894
Are you buying me this big meal before breaking some news?

00:20:19.734 --> 00:20:22.364
What? You want to divorce Jeong Han or something?

00:20:51.824 --> 00:20:52.894
Stella.

00:20:53.834 --> 00:20:56.164
Are you sure it's okay for you to be here?

00:20:56.764 --> 00:20:59.504
Your husband was suspicious and started tracking your location.

00:20:59.904 --> 00:21:01.804
You couldn't visit after that, could you?

00:21:03.774 --> 00:21:04.944
The location tracking...

00:21:06.114 --> 00:21:07.274
I turned it off.

00:21:07.614 --> 00:21:08.814
Is something wrong?

00:21:09.514 --> 00:21:12.444
Don't tell me you're not planning on going home.

00:21:21.194 --> 00:21:22.194
Sister.

00:21:23.194 --> 00:21:25.064
I have a favor to ask you.

00:21:30.034 --> 00:21:31.204
Just eat what's here.

00:21:31.564 --> 00:21:33.834
You've eaten like royalty each morning for over a decade.

00:21:33.834 --> 00:21:36.144
It won't kill you to eat like this for one day.

00:21:36.504 --> 00:21:39.574
But we don't know if it's 1 day, 2, or even 3.

00:21:41.414 --> 00:21:44.684
Go down to the police station and file a missing person's report.

00:21:44.944 --> 00:21:47.154
What? Grandfather, come on.

00:21:47.154 --> 00:21:50.184
This is so annoying! There aren't any clean towels in the bathroom!

00:21:50.184 --> 00:21:52.924
I put the laundry out ages ago. Unbelievable.

00:21:56.664 --> 00:21:58.694
- Look at the state of you! - What?

00:21:58.924 --> 00:22:01.264
Dad, why come out while you're shaving?

00:22:01.264 --> 00:22:03.104
At least wipe your face.

00:22:03.834 --> 00:22:08.474
- I did? - Did Stepmom always help you shave?

00:22:08.904 --> 00:22:11.344
What? Hey.

00:22:12.344 --> 00:22:14.214
Does anyone know where my underwear is?

00:22:14.514 --> 00:22:16.214
Dad, have you lost your mind?

00:22:16.584 --> 00:22:20.284
This is exactly why you need to report her missing and find her.

00:22:20.684 --> 00:22:23.484
We'll look for her after we eat. Here, hurry up and eat. Eat.

00:22:23.684 --> 00:22:25.124
And what are you going to do when you find her?

00:22:25.754 --> 00:22:28.754
Ask her to cook for you, do laundry, and shave your face for you?

00:22:29.464 --> 00:22:33.834
Does anyone here even know what our stepmom's favorite food is?

00:22:35.834 --> 00:22:39.264
Now that you mention it, I don't think I know either.

00:22:40.274 --> 00:22:43.044
Her meals were just tasting the food as she cooked.

00:22:43.904 --> 00:22:45.774
And she'd eat some of the leftovers while cleaning up.

00:22:47.644 --> 00:22:49.684
How can you all be so awful?

00:22:50.384 --> 00:22:53.314
She's only been gone for one day, and the house is already a mess.

00:22:54.114 --> 00:22:58.054
How can you leave her out of such an important decision?

00:22:58.554 --> 00:23:02.794
He's right. I'd feel left out, too.

00:23:03.994 --> 00:23:04.994
If she comes back,

00:23:05.624 --> 00:23:06.864
I swear I'll change.

00:23:07.794 --> 00:23:08.894
You really mean that?

00:23:09.294 --> 00:23:10.334
Of course, I do.

00:23:11.434 --> 00:23:14.574
- Will you change, Grandfather? - Yes!

00:23:15.334 --> 00:23:16.344
Eun Bin, what about you?

00:23:19.474 --> 00:23:21.544
You know where she is, don't you?

00:23:22.544 --> 00:23:24.414
Where is she? Is she okay?

00:23:24.744 --> 00:23:27.084
Is she coming back? Is she coming home?

00:23:28.014 --> 00:23:31.324
She's okay, but I'm not sure if she'll come back.

00:23:36.524 --> 00:23:38.924
But if she does decide to come back,

00:23:39.534 --> 00:23:42.134
every one of you needs to change. Got it?

00:23:58.984 --> 00:24:00.254
(Father-in-law)

00:24:00.354 --> 00:24:04.554
What can I do to make it up to you? Just tell me.

00:24:06.694 --> 00:24:08.394
The house feels so empty without you.

00:24:09.094 --> 00:24:10.424
Please come back.

00:24:12.494 --> 00:24:14.094
I understand why you're upset.

00:24:14.364 --> 00:24:17.634
This is enough. Please come back. You're killing my brother.

00:24:21.074 --> 00:24:24.174
I'm sorry for being so mean to you on purpose.

00:24:24.544 --> 00:24:28.344
I'll be good from now on. Please come back. Please?

00:24:30.984 --> 00:24:32.614
(My Dr. Yang)

00:24:32.614 --> 00:24:33.654
I'm sorry, Se Ri.

00:24:34.254 --> 00:24:36.784
From now on, I'll never do anything you don't want me to.

00:24:37.354 --> 00:24:39.524
I swear on my love for you.

00:24:52.104 --> 00:24:54.434
Judging by your expression, I don't have to worry.

00:24:56.404 --> 00:24:57.404
That's right.

00:24:59.574 --> 00:25:00.574
I think...

00:25:01.314 --> 00:25:02.944
I'm doing all right.

00:25:09.754 --> 00:25:10.754
But...

00:25:13.724 --> 00:25:16.194
I'm not the only one doing okay, am I, Sister?

00:25:34.044 --> 00:25:37.484
Mother. You're not disappointed...

00:25:38.184 --> 00:25:39.514
that I'm more successful than your son?

00:25:40.184 --> 00:25:41.414
My goodness.

00:25:42.784 --> 00:25:46.054
What in the world are you talking about?

00:25:48.594 --> 00:25:51.764
I took out loans and even used my brother-in-law's deposit...

00:25:52.094 --> 00:25:54.294
just to open my own clinic in Seoul.

00:25:54.834 --> 00:25:58.534
And now, I'm on TV, shooting commercials and modeling.

00:25:59.204 --> 00:26:00.734
You're not upset about any of that?

00:26:02.834 --> 00:26:06.644
Someone at the market did ask if I was getting dementia.

00:26:07.374 --> 00:26:10.544
They wondered why I'd give it all to my daughter-in-law, not my son.

00:26:10.844 --> 00:26:12.314
Exactly!

00:26:12.644 --> 00:26:14.914
What mother-in-law would do that for her daughter-in-law?

00:26:15.284 --> 00:26:18.154
How could I be your mother-in-law? I'm your mother.

00:26:19.854 --> 00:26:24.294
When your grandma passed, I made her a solemn promise.

00:26:24.924 --> 00:26:28.564
That I'd raise you as my daughter so she wouldn't have to worry.

00:26:29.264 --> 00:26:32.004
That's why you're my daughter.

00:26:33.474 --> 00:26:35.874
If you divorce Jeong Han, you can come and live with me.

00:26:38.274 --> 00:26:40.914
Should I really divorce him?

00:26:41.374 --> 00:26:43.384
Should I divorce him and just live with you?

00:26:44.284 --> 00:26:45.514
If you want to, go ahead.

00:26:46.114 --> 00:26:47.314
I won't stop you.

00:26:49.254 --> 00:26:52.024
You're saying that because you know I can't do it, aren't you?

00:26:52.554 --> 00:26:53.754
What? Why not?

00:26:53.994 --> 00:26:57.994
What, is there some rule that says a family counselor can't divorce?

00:26:58.564 --> 00:27:01.794
By that logic, can doctors not get sick?

00:27:02.234 --> 00:27:04.704
And schoolteachers' kids all have to be straight-A students?

00:27:06.434 --> 00:27:10.004
Wow, that abalone porridge really lit a fire under you.

00:27:11.574 --> 00:27:12.604
Or...

00:27:14.114 --> 00:27:17.314
Let's leave Jeong Han in Onjeong and move away, just the two of us.

00:27:28.354 --> 00:27:30.194
What's upsetting you the most?

00:27:30.764 --> 00:27:33.534
Go on, tell me. We can bad-mouth my son.

00:27:36.264 --> 00:27:38.464
I saw Dr. Yang yesterday,

00:27:40.104 --> 00:27:43.344
and he said I don't understand my husband's feelings.

00:27:44.544 --> 00:27:45.574
The nerve of that guy.

00:27:46.304 --> 00:27:49.744
He should be confiding in his wife. He's so nosy...

00:27:50.914 --> 00:27:54.254
But the thing is, I knew how Jeong Han felt.

00:27:55.754 --> 00:27:59.994
But I liked that he was doing what I wanted.

00:28:00.694 --> 00:28:05.324
And here I am, someone who reads hearts and prescribes love,

00:28:07.334 --> 00:28:09.864
yet I pretended not to understand what my own husband was feeling.

00:28:11.234 --> 00:28:12.704
I was so ashamed of myself.

00:28:32.854 --> 00:28:35.624
Yes, thank you. I'll really enjoy this.

00:28:36.124 --> 00:28:37.124
What?

00:28:37.664 --> 00:28:39.764
Officer Jung, you're out grocery shopping too.

00:28:40.034 --> 00:28:41.894
Yes. It's my day off.

00:28:42.894 --> 00:28:45.064
Wait, why the long face?

00:28:46.034 --> 00:28:50.904
Dr. Gong changed his mind. He says they're moving after all.

00:28:53.644 --> 00:28:56.684
He changes his mind so often, I can't keep track anymore.

00:28:57.214 --> 00:28:58.214
Hang on a second.

00:28:58.784 --> 00:28:59.784
So then,

00:29:00.114 --> 00:29:02.414
what does that mean for you, Nurse Oh?

00:29:03.124 --> 00:29:05.524
I think I'm just going to take some time off.

00:29:08.594 --> 00:29:12.364
I guess I won't be seeing you around as much then.

00:29:13.064 --> 00:29:17.204
I live nearby, so I'll come here to get groceries from time to time.

00:29:18.504 --> 00:29:19.804
I should get going.

00:29:20.534 --> 00:29:21.534
Okay.

00:29:31.484 --> 00:29:32.684
Sauce on the side or all over?

00:29:34.014 --> 00:29:36.624
- The drench-and-sog. - What's that?

00:29:37.254 --> 00:29:39.624
Here, watch. Like this.

00:29:39.854 --> 00:29:43.394
You drench it, and then eat it when it gets soggy.

00:29:44.764 --> 00:29:46.764
See? I knew we had the same taste in food.

00:29:51.164 --> 00:29:52.664
Get nice and soggy.

00:29:54.934 --> 00:29:58.074
You know why I got shot down on that blind date?

00:29:59.104 --> 00:30:02.414
So Hye's brother just has bad taste? Not that I'm complaining.

00:30:03.914 --> 00:30:06.144
No, our tastes in food were just way too different.

00:30:06.284 --> 00:30:10.424
He was cutting fat off the pork belly with scissors.

00:30:10.484 --> 00:30:13.894
What? Seriously? That's basically a crime, isn't it?

00:30:13.994 --> 00:30:15.294
Lock him up.

00:30:16.254 --> 00:30:19.064
On top of that, he doesn't drink. And get this.

00:30:19.124 --> 00:30:23.564
- He doesn't eat carbs either. - What? He deserves a life sentence.

00:30:29.134 --> 00:30:31.744
Why didn't your blind date work out, Director?

00:30:32.874 --> 00:30:35.414
It wasn't a blind date. She was just...

00:30:35.644 --> 00:30:38.214
someone I know through my stepmother.

00:30:39.684 --> 00:30:44.054
Your stepmother... She wants you to get married?

00:30:44.284 --> 00:30:48.994
Yes. She thinks if I get married, then I'll decide to stay in Korea.

00:30:52.694 --> 00:30:55.364
Hurry up and eat. We have somewhere to go after this.

00:30:56.534 --> 00:30:57.534
Okay.

00:30:59.164 --> 00:31:01.174
This looks delicious.

00:31:01.234 --> 00:31:03.104
(3H Acupressure Beds)

00:31:04.374 --> 00:31:05.644
Welcome.

00:31:08.914 --> 00:31:12.644
Why are we here? Shopping for our first home?

00:31:12.944 --> 00:31:13.954
What?

00:31:15.054 --> 00:31:19.324
I'm kidding. Why the big eyes? We're a couple, so what?

00:31:19.384 --> 00:31:22.054
You really got me there. You totally threw me off.

00:31:23.224 --> 00:31:25.294
Seriously, though, why did you bring me here?

00:31:25.794 --> 00:31:29.594
When my stepmother returns, I want them to be like newlyweds,

00:31:29.664 --> 00:31:30.964
so I thought I'd get them a new bed.

00:31:33.134 --> 00:31:35.134
They've got quite a selection here.

00:31:35.934 --> 00:31:38.504
- Please, try it out. - Should I?

00:31:39.174 --> 00:31:40.174
Sure.

00:31:41.644 --> 00:31:42.674
Come.

00:31:44.944 --> 00:31:46.684
(3H Acupressure Beds)

00:31:48.384 --> 00:31:49.654
This one's nice.

00:31:50.324 --> 00:31:51.754
It really is.

00:31:53.024 --> 00:31:55.124
I thought I'd throw a little party for my mom when she comes.

00:31:55.124 --> 00:31:57.124
You know, a little welcome home event.

00:31:57.224 --> 00:32:00.034
A party? Do you have any good ideas?

00:32:02.534 --> 00:32:04.734
(Party and Event Supply Kits)

00:32:05.504 --> 00:32:06.604
This is it.

00:32:10.374 --> 00:32:11.374
Ta-da!

00:32:12.544 --> 00:32:15.974
A real-life princess! For you, Princess.

00:32:16.744 --> 00:32:18.314
- How do I look? - The star of the show, Gong Ju Ah.

00:32:18.314 --> 00:32:19.514
Princess Gong Ju Ah.

00:32:19.584 --> 00:32:21.384
- Ta-da! - Oh, right there.

00:32:22.254 --> 00:32:23.254
Here.

00:32:38.264 --> 00:32:39.264
What?

00:32:39.564 --> 00:32:42.574
I said I'm so happy, it feels like I'm dreaming.

00:32:43.974 --> 00:32:47.644
Right, I had a dream that you were planning a surprise event for me.

00:32:48.144 --> 00:32:50.114
Me, in your dream? I was planning an event?

00:32:53.214 --> 00:32:54.914
I've got a great idea.

00:33:19.074 --> 00:33:21.974
I'm on top of the world

00:33:22.044 --> 00:33:25.444
With the woman who loves me

00:33:25.914 --> 00:33:28.484
With my Cha Se Ri

00:33:28.984 --> 00:33:33.894
I want to walk my own path, I really do

00:33:47.074 --> 00:33:48.134
So, how's it going?

00:33:48.704 --> 00:33:51.204
You studied abroad. This is the best you could come up with?

00:33:51.274 --> 00:33:54.014
Shoot, they said this would work. That it's every woman's fantasy.

00:33:54.114 --> 00:33:56.574
Hey, who told you that? This is too cringe-worthy to watch.

00:33:57.044 --> 00:33:58.584
Aunt does not look impressed.

00:34:00.554 --> 00:34:03.354
I have been so lonely and had such a hard time

00:34:03.454 --> 00:34:06.924
But it's only a rehearsal

00:34:07.454 --> 00:34:10.864
I'm not going to fall down

00:34:10.994 --> 00:34:13.434
We got this

00:34:15.494 --> 00:34:16.564
I'm sorry, Se Ri.

00:34:17.304 --> 00:34:19.834
I'll never make you feel lonely again...

00:34:20.774 --> 00:34:21.934
Honey.

00:34:22.534 --> 00:34:26.404
- Se Ri, I'm sorry. - Honey.

00:34:26.814 --> 00:34:27.914
I love you.

00:34:44.924 --> 00:34:46.794
One, two, three!

00:34:47.494 --> 00:34:49.494
- Ta-da! - Ta-da!

00:34:49.664 --> 00:34:55.174
(We're sorry.)

00:35:01.614 --> 00:35:04.444
- We're sorry. - We're so sorry.

00:35:18.194 --> 00:35:21.534
- Han Seong Mi! - Han Seong Mi!

00:35:21.594 --> 00:35:25.934
- Han Seong Mi! - Han Seong Mi!

00:35:36.984 --> 00:35:43.354
The single, clear tear in your eye

00:35:44.254 --> 00:35:47.994
Makes my heart pound

00:35:48.254 --> 00:35:52.094
It pounds

00:35:53.024 --> 00:35:55.394
- Thump, thump, thump - Thump, thump, thump

00:35:55.694 --> 00:35:58.004
- You are my personal IV drip - You are my personal IV drip

00:35:58.004 --> 00:36:01.074
- My very own intravenous shot - My very own intravenous shot

00:36:01.174 --> 00:36:06.044
- You're the cure for my arrhythmia - You're the cure for my arrhythmia

00:36:06.144 --> 00:36:07.914
- You are my IV drip - You are my IV drip

00:36:07.914 --> 00:36:10.684
- My personal Band-Aid - My personal Band-Aid

00:36:11.014 --> 00:36:15.454
- You heal all my wounds - You heal all my wounds

00:36:18.984 --> 00:36:22.754
Hey, Seong Mi.

00:36:24.594 --> 00:36:25.694
You.

00:36:26.594 --> 00:36:27.594
Let's talk inside.

00:36:38.404 --> 00:36:41.914
- Grandma, is Mom still mad? - Does Mom...

00:36:42.214 --> 00:36:43.474
really want a divorce?

00:36:50.624 --> 00:36:52.054
(The Cutest Ever)

00:36:55.394 --> 00:36:57.094
We'll move. All right?

00:36:58.364 --> 00:37:00.894
Come on, stop being so mad, Seong Mi.

00:37:01.994 --> 00:37:03.904
Do you really mean that?

00:37:04.334 --> 00:37:08.834
Yes, I do. I've already called the hospitals to refer my patients,

00:37:08.904 --> 00:37:12.944
and the senior companion service... I took care of it all.

00:37:13.204 --> 00:37:16.314
See? Even now, you're listing your actions and duties...

00:37:16.474 --> 00:37:18.744
just to protect your own ego.

00:37:19.314 --> 00:37:22.784
Hey, why do you have to analyze everything?

00:37:23.384 --> 00:37:26.154
Why can't you just tell me how you really feel?

00:37:26.784 --> 00:37:30.264
Why do I have to hear how you feel from other people?

00:37:30.394 --> 00:37:32.724
Why do you keep making me out to be the bad guy?

00:37:33.224 --> 00:37:36.594
This is classic passive-aggressive behavior.

00:37:37.704 --> 00:37:39.534
What? How am I being...

00:37:41.534 --> 00:37:42.574
Tell me.

00:37:43.204 --> 00:37:44.774
Tell me why you had second thoughts.

00:37:48.244 --> 00:37:50.074
Please, just tell me.

00:37:50.584 --> 00:37:51.644
Please? Honey.

00:38:00.654 --> 00:38:02.554
I had a job interview,

00:38:03.124 --> 00:38:04.724
and I was a little scared.

00:38:06.064 --> 00:38:09.134
I guess it's because I've been in Onjeong for so long.

00:38:10.304 --> 00:38:12.304
I started wondering if I could adapt to somewhere new,

00:38:13.234 --> 00:38:17.044
if I could even pull my own weight at my age.

00:38:17.804 --> 00:38:19.574
Those thoughts just made me feel a bit...

00:38:20.144 --> 00:38:21.314
I got scared.

00:38:25.284 --> 00:38:27.654
Then why did you want to be on "Human Theater?"

00:38:28.254 --> 00:38:33.084
When I asked you to do a show, you insisted you weren't fit for TV.

00:38:33.624 --> 00:38:34.624
Well, that's...

00:38:35.254 --> 00:38:37.724
Bucket said something to me.

00:38:38.664 --> 00:38:40.894
I want to proudly show them how I'm doing.

00:38:41.334 --> 00:38:44.664
How well the children they abandoned are doing,

00:38:45.404 --> 00:38:47.004
how well my kids have grown up...

00:38:48.074 --> 00:38:50.504
I just want to proudly show them what they're missing.

00:38:54.774 --> 00:38:56.114
When I heard him say that,

00:38:57.014 --> 00:38:59.614
it made me think of my own father.

00:39:00.684 --> 00:39:04.084
I can't even film that vlog with you anymore.

00:39:04.824 --> 00:39:07.994
Since a lot of older people watch "Human Theater,"

00:39:09.024 --> 00:39:10.024
I thought that wherever he is,

00:39:10.824 --> 00:39:13.764
my father might happen to see it.

00:39:17.364 --> 00:39:18.534
That's right.

00:39:19.634 --> 00:39:21.834
That I'm still running our clinic...

00:39:22.604 --> 00:39:23.744
even without my father...

00:39:24.644 --> 00:39:27.774
That I'm still here in Onjeong, keeping it going strong.

00:39:28.914 --> 00:39:30.914
I guess that's what I wanted to show him.

00:39:33.514 --> 00:39:34.914
I'm sorry, Seong Mi.

00:39:52.504 --> 00:39:55.334
What did you call me here to talk about?

00:39:57.244 --> 00:39:58.404
To be honest,

00:39:59.904 --> 00:40:01.314
I really...

00:40:02.214 --> 00:40:05.744
I truly can't stand you.

00:40:07.784 --> 00:40:09.084
When I see you,

00:40:10.784 --> 00:40:14.024
it just reminds me of how inadequate I am.

00:40:16.624 --> 00:40:17.624
Until I...

00:40:18.164 --> 00:40:19.824
became an adult,

00:40:21.394 --> 00:40:22.894
I lived in an orphanage...

00:40:24.004 --> 00:40:25.564
that was run by a convent.

00:40:29.134 --> 00:40:30.874
I'm not highly educated,

00:40:32.304 --> 00:40:33.544
and the only thing I really have...

00:40:34.644 --> 00:40:38.614
is this pretty face, as you can see.

00:40:40.214 --> 00:40:43.714
Seeing you made me so envious,

00:40:46.224 --> 00:40:47.824
and it made me so jealous...

00:40:49.154 --> 00:40:50.194
that I've grown to resent you.

00:40:52.224 --> 00:40:54.064
So I used what happened to Dong Suk as an excuse...

00:40:54.794 --> 00:40:56.394
to try and make you move away.

00:40:58.834 --> 00:41:00.434
But I realized that my own selfishness...

00:41:01.574 --> 00:41:05.404
shouldn't stand in the way of what my husband wants.

00:41:07.104 --> 00:41:10.274
For the way I crossed the line with my words and actions last time,

00:41:11.144 --> 00:41:12.514
I'm not going to beg you...

00:41:13.644 --> 00:41:15.314
to forgive me.

00:41:16.554 --> 00:41:19.484
Because that would be selfish of me, too.

00:41:21.394 --> 00:41:22.494
I...

00:41:23.354 --> 00:41:26.564
I'm asking you with all my heart, Doctor.

00:41:27.864 --> 00:41:28.934
About Dr. Gong...

00:41:29.294 --> 00:41:32.334
appearing on "Human Theater" with Dr. Yang,

00:41:34.034 --> 00:41:36.234
couldn't you please give him your permission?

00:41:43.674 --> 00:41:45.414
Give me some time to think it over.

00:41:47.554 --> 00:41:50.014
Of course. Thank you.

00:42:00.394 --> 00:42:03.734
My parents also passed away when I was in elementary school,

00:42:04.004 --> 00:42:07.634
so I was raised by my grandmother before I got married at a young age.

00:42:08.574 --> 00:42:10.334
I was very fortunate...

00:42:10.674 --> 00:42:13.074
that my mother-in-law made sure I could continue my studies.

00:42:14.714 --> 00:42:16.674
If there's one difference between us,

00:42:17.014 --> 00:42:18.414
it would be our level of education.

00:42:19.914 --> 00:42:21.414
If you feel you've missed out on that,

00:42:25.254 --> 00:42:27.054
I don't think it's too late to change that.

00:42:31.794 --> 00:42:33.064
If I'm out of line for saying so,

00:42:33.864 --> 00:42:34.864
I apologize.

00:42:36.894 --> 00:42:39.564
Thank you for the advice.

00:42:55.354 --> 00:42:56.384
In that case,

00:42:57.254 --> 00:43:00.354
let's all decide this with a majority vote.

00:43:01.554 --> 00:43:04.064
All those who want to move, raise your hand.

00:43:06.964 --> 00:43:09.494
What? It's just you and me, Dad?

00:43:10.264 --> 00:43:12.464
It looks that way.

00:43:12.864 --> 00:43:15.834
Put your hand down, Gong Jeong Han. You're not fooling anyone.

00:43:16.104 --> 00:43:20.104
But I really want to move! Come on! I'm serious, I really am!

00:43:20.104 --> 00:43:22.574
But Woo Jae, I thought you wanted to move.

00:43:23.014 --> 00:43:25.684
Hey, raise your hand. Come on, do it.

00:43:26.744 --> 00:43:27.784
I'm not going to.

00:43:28.454 --> 00:43:29.454
You're the one who told me...

00:43:29.854 --> 00:43:31.554
not to live the life Mom wants for me,

00:43:32.154 --> 00:43:33.854
but to live the life I want.

00:43:34.124 --> 00:43:37.564
Hey, Gong Woo Jae. Why are you bringing that up now?

00:43:38.194 --> 00:43:39.524
What are you talking about?

00:43:43.464 --> 00:43:45.164
I'm in therapy.

00:43:45.464 --> 00:43:46.464
What?

00:43:46.864 --> 00:43:48.204
- What? What was that? - What do you mean?

00:43:48.274 --> 00:43:49.274
Since when?

00:43:49.774 --> 00:43:50.774
For a while now.

00:43:52.374 --> 00:43:53.774
I'm sure you all saw it coming.

00:43:54.274 --> 00:43:57.044
I was top of my med school class, but I still can't get my license.

00:43:57.514 --> 00:44:00.854
- It's no surprise I'm not okay. - Oh, Woo Jae.

00:44:01.354 --> 00:44:02.554
I'm sorry, Grandma.

00:44:05.354 --> 00:44:06.584
You knew about this?

00:44:07.254 --> 00:44:09.654
What? Yes.

00:44:10.354 --> 00:44:11.364
Gong Ju Ah, you too?

00:44:11.824 --> 00:44:15.064
He said he'd tell you himself once you were feeling better, Mom.

00:44:17.764 --> 00:44:18.764
So...

00:44:19.334 --> 00:44:22.134
Woo Jae, are you going to quit, just like Ju Ah?

00:44:23.974 --> 00:44:26.104
Mom, I've dreamed of...

00:44:26.204 --> 00:44:28.474
becoming a doctor ever since I was in your womb.

00:44:28.914 --> 00:44:32.414
I want to be a fourth-generation doctor and run our clinic.

00:44:33.684 --> 00:44:34.684
That's my nephew.

00:44:35.714 --> 00:44:39.224
If you feel that way, why didn't you say so about moving?

00:44:40.754 --> 00:44:42.924
I wanted to come clean when I had a chance like this.

00:44:44.064 --> 00:44:46.764
You're all really making me out to be the bad guy.

00:44:47.894 --> 00:44:48.994
What about you, Dae Han?

00:44:49.534 --> 00:44:52.034
Are you really okay with not moving?

00:44:53.104 --> 00:44:56.074
Yes. I never wanted to move anyway.

00:44:57.744 --> 00:44:58.744
Well, then...

00:44:59.744 --> 00:45:02.974
Let's pretend this conversation never happened...

00:45:03.774 --> 00:45:07.184
and officially decide we're not moving.

00:45:07.914 --> 00:45:09.754
Gosh, this is so annoying.

00:45:11.454 --> 00:45:13.224
Woo Jae, come with me.

00:45:22.394 --> 00:45:24.434
- Are you happy now? - Happy?

00:45:25.164 --> 00:45:26.164
What?

00:45:27.334 --> 00:45:30.674
Well, yes. I'm happy. So what? What are you going to do? Goodness.

00:45:30.744 --> 00:45:33.174
Yes! I don't have to move!

00:45:34.374 --> 00:45:36.574
Uncle, what are you so happy about?

00:45:36.644 --> 00:45:39.944
I don't know! I just... I'm just happy, that's all!

00:45:48.754 --> 00:45:49.754
Really?

00:45:50.594 --> 00:45:55.594
Yes. I'm fine with them not moving.

00:45:57.134 --> 00:45:59.504
So Dr. Gong's whole family has agreed to it?

00:45:59.834 --> 00:46:04.144
Yes. They had a family meeting. Not moving and being on the show...

00:46:04.204 --> 00:46:05.874
They called and said yes to all of it.

00:46:07.844 --> 00:46:09.044
Thank you so much.

00:46:09.474 --> 00:46:11.084
I know it couldn't have been easy for you to ask them.

00:46:11.444 --> 00:46:13.084
See, Dad?

00:46:13.384 --> 00:46:15.284
In the end, it took my stepmom to get things done.

00:46:15.454 --> 00:46:17.314
No, that's not it, Hyun Bin.

00:46:17.654 --> 00:46:20.754
It's just like Eun Bin said. I was blinded by jealousy...

00:46:20.954 --> 00:46:22.954
and almost made us miss out on a great opportunity.

00:46:23.994 --> 00:46:25.994
Thank you so much, Stepmom.

00:46:26.764 --> 00:46:27.764
Thank you, Se Ri.

00:46:28.164 --> 00:46:31.264
For you, I'm going to become the biggest star in the universe,

00:46:31.334 --> 00:46:34.134
and I'll take the country by storm. I swear.

00:46:34.404 --> 00:46:36.534
Yes! Bring it on!

00:46:37.434 --> 00:46:39.244
- My goodness. - How will you take them by storm?

00:46:39.304 --> 00:46:41.614
What? I'll just... I'll blow them all away.

00:46:48.754 --> 00:46:51.584
What? Seong Mi.

00:46:52.124 --> 00:46:54.124
Did you separate the beds?

00:46:55.254 --> 00:46:57.964
Yes. I can't even stand the sight of you,

00:46:58.024 --> 00:47:00.324
and I thought I might just kill you if we had to touch.

00:47:03.294 --> 00:47:04.464
My gosh, but...

00:47:04.804 --> 00:47:08.474
I'd completely forgotten this was two single beds pushed together.

00:47:09.404 --> 00:47:11.974
Is that right? I never forgot. Not once.

00:47:13.404 --> 00:47:16.074
But you agreed to everything.

00:47:16.144 --> 00:47:18.814
Doesn't that mean you're not angry anymore?

00:47:20.114 --> 00:47:21.184
Don't kid yourself.

00:47:21.714 --> 00:47:25.184
I knew I couldn't sleep at night if we moved knowing how you felt.

00:47:25.284 --> 00:47:27.024
So it was a decision I had to force myself to make.

00:47:27.624 --> 00:47:30.024
Hey, but if you're going to be like this,

00:47:30.454 --> 00:47:33.064
then I'm the one who can't sleep peacefully.

00:47:34.064 --> 00:47:37.194
You got everything you wanted. You expect to sleep soundly, too?

00:47:38.204 --> 00:47:39.204
Just turn off the light.

00:47:41.774 --> 00:47:44.344
Right, the light. Turning it off.

00:47:49.344 --> 00:47:53.344
Are you sure you'll be okay with Jeong Han's family not moving?

00:47:55.114 --> 00:47:57.824
If you're happy, I'm happy.

00:47:59.254 --> 00:48:00.454
But I thought the psychic...

00:48:00.894 --> 00:48:02.094
told you to stay away from the Gongs.

00:48:02.994 --> 00:48:04.424
About that...

00:48:05.194 --> 00:48:07.424
She actually said to stay away from round balls.

00:48:07.894 --> 00:48:08.894
Round balls?

00:48:09.694 --> 00:48:12.334
Like basketballs, golf balls, and things like that?

00:48:13.364 --> 00:48:16.904
Yes. I just mistakenly thought she meant the Gong family.

00:48:17.904 --> 00:48:19.904
I'll make sure to dodge any balls from now on.

00:48:20.274 --> 00:48:21.844
I'll block them all for you.

00:48:23.944 --> 00:48:27.144
This made me realize something all over again.

00:48:27.784 --> 00:48:31.384
That I just can't live without you.

00:48:32.684 --> 00:48:33.684
Me too.

00:48:34.054 --> 00:48:36.494
I'm never leaving this house again.

00:48:47.804 --> 00:48:50.304
To a completely successful event.

00:48:50.604 --> 00:48:53.344
Well, I don't think ours was that great.

00:48:53.404 --> 00:48:55.144
Come on, it all worked out in the end.

00:49:01.714 --> 00:49:04.684
There's something I'm curious about.

00:49:06.084 --> 00:49:08.594
Are we only dating for one year?

00:49:09.354 --> 00:49:11.464
- What? - Well...

00:49:11.464 --> 00:49:14.024
You'll go back to Argentina in a year.

00:49:14.394 --> 00:49:17.664
That's ridiculous. How long have you thought this?

00:49:17.804 --> 00:49:20.304
Don't tell me you've been thinking about this ever since I confessed.

00:49:21.274 --> 00:49:22.274
Yes.

00:49:23.734 --> 00:49:26.444
What? I'm not going anywhere. I'm planting myself right here.

00:49:26.504 --> 00:49:28.114
I wouldn't leave even if you pushed me out the door.

00:49:28.274 --> 00:49:31.514
You're Pacu Nacho Yang, the global brand director.

00:49:32.114 --> 00:49:35.214
Why would a global talent like you stay here? It's a waste.

00:49:35.284 --> 00:49:37.784
Who says you have to be overseas to be global?

00:49:37.784 --> 00:49:40.084
I can just help K-brands go global.

00:49:40.424 --> 00:49:44.724
Gosh, I just don't want to hold a successful director back.

00:49:45.064 --> 00:49:47.894
Don't tell me you only want to date me for a year.

00:49:48.194 --> 00:49:49.494
Wouldn't that be for the best?

00:49:49.934 --> 00:49:52.134
Besides, there's the whole issue with our parents.

00:49:53.634 --> 00:49:55.174
Fine. Then I'm not dating you at all.

00:49:56.604 --> 00:49:59.344
Why do you have to be so dramatic? Goodness.

00:49:59.404 --> 00:50:03.274
My dream is to marry Gong Ju Ah and live happily ever after.

00:50:03.374 --> 00:50:06.714
What? Who says you can? Goodness.

00:50:07.144 --> 00:50:09.584
I said we could date. Who said anything about marriage?

00:50:09.984 --> 00:50:11.184
If you're going to get married,

00:50:11.184 --> 00:50:12.984
you should date someone through all four seasons...

00:50:13.054 --> 00:50:14.754
before making that kind of decision.

00:50:14.824 --> 00:50:18.524
I bet you won't even last one season before you want to marry me.

00:50:19.564 --> 00:50:20.794
We'll see about that.

00:50:21.764 --> 00:50:26.234
I'm a marketing expert. I'm confident I can win anyone over.

00:50:26.304 --> 00:50:29.074
I'm pretty sure your family will fall in love with me.

00:50:29.474 --> 00:50:30.474
Oh, no.

00:50:30.834 --> 00:50:33.004
My mom's coming to the office next week.

00:50:33.474 --> 00:50:35.514
Now, I'm worried you're going to pull a stunt.

00:50:36.644 --> 00:50:39.184
Wow, you don't know me at all, do you?

00:50:39.644 --> 00:50:42.114
Just wait and see what I do.

00:50:43.584 --> 00:50:46.124
And another thing, I don't want an office romance.

00:50:46.624 --> 00:50:48.554
And I hate people gossiping about me.

00:50:48.754 --> 00:50:51.264
Yes, I agree with that.

00:50:53.194 --> 00:50:56.364
Then should we come up with some ground rules?

00:50:58.064 --> 00:51:00.004
Ground rules for a secret relationship?

00:51:04.304 --> 00:51:05.374
Hold on!

00:51:07.274 --> 00:51:08.574
(Arriving at and leaving work)

00:51:08.644 --> 00:51:11.114
We should arrive at work and leave at different times.

00:51:11.444 --> 00:51:14.244
The more our paths cross, the higher the risk of being caught.

00:51:14.584 --> 00:51:16.914
And what if we happen to run into each other?

00:51:17.484 --> 00:51:21.394
We maintain a proper distance and act strictly as colleagues.

00:51:23.124 --> 00:51:24.354
(Meetings)

00:51:24.424 --> 00:51:26.994
We act strictly professional during meetings, too.

00:51:27.934 --> 00:51:30.394
I trust your presentation is coming along well?

00:51:30.964 --> 00:51:33.104
We ran a rehearsal based on your revisions from this morning.

00:51:33.264 --> 00:51:36.304
The pacing and message delivery were both clean and effective.

00:51:41.214 --> 00:51:43.514
Hey, no googly eyes!

00:51:44.914 --> 00:51:46.414
Let's hope for a good outcome.

00:51:48.014 --> 00:51:51.224
In the cafeteria, we must always sit apart.

00:51:54.724 --> 00:51:57.224
Did anything interesting happen over the weekend?

00:51:58.894 --> 00:52:00.724
I literally slept all day.

00:52:01.364 --> 00:52:03.264
Gosh, I must be getting old.

00:52:03.494 --> 00:52:06.704
Be careful. The VP and Mr. Park will grill us.

00:52:07.234 --> 00:52:08.974
So, any progress with Gong Ju Ah?

00:52:10.074 --> 00:52:12.444
Aren't you curious about what happened that night?

00:52:12.674 --> 00:52:15.274
Wow, the smoky aroma is amazing.

00:52:27.354 --> 00:52:29.324
Oh, that was perfect.

00:52:30.124 --> 00:52:31.964
I don't think they suspect a thing, do you?

00:52:32.364 --> 00:52:33.824
Of course not. Not a thing.

00:52:34.664 --> 00:52:37.434
The thought that we're dating would never even cross their minds.

00:52:42.234 --> 00:52:43.534
They're definitely dating.

00:52:43.934 --> 00:52:45.604
Yes. A hundred percent.

00:52:46.344 --> 00:52:47.704
Gosh, but...

00:52:48.274 --> 00:52:50.974
It's unclear if it's just a thing, or if they're officially a couple.

00:52:52.614 --> 00:52:55.484
You'll probably find that out tomorrow.

00:52:55.684 --> 00:53:00.484
- Tomorrow? Why? - I've been debating it all weekend.

00:53:00.854 --> 00:53:03.294
About whether I should tell you or not.

00:53:04.564 --> 00:53:06.124
I put my friendship with Ms. Gong on one side...

00:53:07.024 --> 00:53:09.634
and the fate of the Fashion Division on the other.

00:53:10.234 --> 00:53:13.634
And let's just say, the scales tipped a bit this way.

00:53:14.034 --> 00:53:15.474
Gosh, why so serious?

00:53:17.404 --> 00:53:20.374
- You know Dr. Han Seong Mi, right? - Yes.

00:53:22.214 --> 00:53:23.914
She's Ms. Gong's mother.

00:53:26.244 --> 00:53:27.244
Getting excited?

00:53:29.254 --> 00:53:30.254
My goodness.

00:53:31.154 --> 00:53:33.454
Am I allowed to have this much fun at work?

00:53:34.054 --> 00:53:35.024
My gosh!

00:53:41.194 --> 00:53:44.534
- What? What's wrong? - Who is it? Why?

00:53:44.604 --> 00:53:46.234
- They're not leaving. - What?

00:53:46.804 --> 00:53:48.604
Who's not leaving? What are you talking about?

00:53:48.804 --> 00:53:51.444
- I mean, the move! - Really?

00:53:51.604 --> 00:53:53.644
But I thought they'd already decided not to move.

00:53:53.874 --> 00:53:56.814
Well, they kept going back and forth about it.

00:53:57.114 --> 00:54:00.944
- Wow, that's great news. - I know, right? I'm so happy.

00:54:01.084 --> 00:54:03.114
Yes!

00:54:05.254 --> 00:54:06.254
I have to go!

00:54:11.724 --> 00:54:12.794
Officer Jung, are you okay?

00:54:13.194 --> 00:54:16.234
- Sorry? - I can hear your heart pounding.

00:54:17.664 --> 00:54:21.004
- What do you mean? Goodness. - Come on.

00:54:21.064 --> 00:54:22.904
Step aside! Move, get out of the way.

00:54:29.174 --> 00:54:33.044
I thought we already had an agreement. What happened?

00:54:35.684 --> 00:54:38.024
I don't know when,

00:54:38.854 --> 00:54:41.394
or if that day will even come,

00:54:42.224 --> 00:54:44.664
but if he finds out the clinic and pharmacy are gone,

00:54:45.264 --> 00:54:46.264
Gi Cheol...

00:54:47.464 --> 00:54:49.094
would be disappointed.

00:54:51.764 --> 00:54:53.604
He's the one who vanished.

00:54:54.934 --> 00:54:57.004
What right does he have to be disappointed?

00:54:58.304 --> 00:54:59.304
You're right.

00:55:00.204 --> 00:55:02.774
But anyway, here we are, keeping things going.

00:55:05.214 --> 00:55:06.214
Yes.

00:55:07.184 --> 00:55:11.014
I know Dae Han and Dong Suk must be deeply hurt,

00:55:12.784 --> 00:55:14.924
but I'm sure they'll heal with time.

00:55:15.794 --> 00:55:16.794
Just like we did.

00:55:18.164 --> 00:55:19.394
Let's hope so.

00:55:42.784 --> 00:55:43.784
What do you want?

00:55:44.484 --> 00:55:45.484
You heard, right?

00:55:46.184 --> 00:55:47.354
We're not moving.

00:55:48.024 --> 00:55:51.424
So? Did you call me out here to see if your stomach would still hurt?

00:55:51.694 --> 00:55:53.664
- Yes. - And?

00:55:54.264 --> 00:55:55.334
I feel fine.

00:55:56.194 --> 00:55:57.194
Good for you.

00:55:58.434 --> 00:56:00.534
- I'm off. - Hey, Dong Suk.

00:56:00.934 --> 00:56:01.934
What?

00:56:02.774 --> 00:56:03.874
What kind of shampoo do you use?

00:56:05.144 --> 00:56:07.644
- What? - That day, I noticed...

00:56:08.374 --> 00:56:10.814
your shampoo smelled really nice, and I was thinking of getting some.

00:56:12.744 --> 00:56:14.314
I'll buy some and send it to you.

00:56:14.644 --> 00:56:16.554
You could just send me the link.

00:56:18.284 --> 00:56:19.384
It's my way of saying thanks.

00:56:19.984 --> 00:56:20.984
What?

00:56:21.524 --> 00:56:24.124
I remember everything that happened at the motel now.

00:56:25.324 --> 00:56:26.364
For looking out for me...

00:56:26.894 --> 00:56:28.934
and being so kind... Thank you.

00:56:30.094 --> 00:56:32.304
Then and now,

00:56:33.234 --> 00:56:34.704
you've always been a good person.

00:56:42.214 --> 00:56:43.214
I'm off.

00:56:47.344 --> 00:56:48.354
Okay, bye.

00:56:53.084 --> 00:56:55.294
My stomach doesn't hurt, so why does my heart ache?

00:56:57.024 --> 00:56:58.024
What is this feeling?

00:56:59.824 --> 00:57:01.664
Is this some kind of psychosomatic heart condition?

00:57:02.794 --> 00:57:04.364
- Get home safe. - Okay.

00:57:04.364 --> 00:57:06.564
- And be sure to take your medicine. - I will. Thank you.

00:57:06.634 --> 00:57:07.664
All right, take care.

00:57:09.034 --> 00:57:12.144
Hey. I heard Seong Mi gave you the okay.

00:57:12.504 --> 00:57:14.374
So you're doing "Human Theater," right?

00:57:14.674 --> 00:57:16.474
Thank you, my friend.

00:57:17.674 --> 00:57:19.214
"My friend," my foot.

00:57:20.084 --> 00:57:22.554
"Human Theater?" What's that? Something to eat?

00:57:22.614 --> 00:57:26.684
Hey, I knew you'd be like this, so I wrote down a few more quotes.

00:57:28.154 --> 00:57:31.054
What's this? "How can a person change so much?"

00:57:31.664 --> 00:57:33.694
"Nothing's gone right since I met you?"

00:57:34.294 --> 00:57:36.294
The feeling is mutual, you jerk.

00:57:37.064 --> 00:57:38.704
Hey, come on. Cut me some slack.

00:57:43.074 --> 00:57:45.504
You barely ate all weekend, didn't you?

00:57:46.144 --> 00:57:48.574
I'll make the webfoot octopus for dinner tonight.

00:57:49.574 --> 00:57:50.914
I'm so sorry, Father.

00:57:53.484 --> 00:57:54.514
Listen.

00:57:55.914 --> 00:57:57.814
This is the last meal you'll be making for me.

00:57:58.754 --> 00:58:02.254
- What? - From now on, hire a housekeeper.

00:58:02.954 --> 00:58:05.124
I won't work you like this anymore.

00:58:05.624 --> 00:58:06.624
But...

00:58:07.164 --> 00:58:11.564
I like taking care of a big family, since I grew up without my own.

00:58:11.634 --> 00:58:13.634
I told you that when I got married.

00:58:17.074 --> 00:58:21.714
You were probably just being polite to your lonely old father-in-law.

00:58:22.414 --> 00:58:25.444
And this foolish old man took you at your word and...

00:58:26.344 --> 00:58:27.384
gave you a hard time.

00:58:28.254 --> 00:58:31.554
Hire help. Do as I say. From now on,

00:58:32.424 --> 00:58:33.584
let's take better care of you.

00:58:34.654 --> 00:58:36.994
Then what am I supposed to do?

00:58:39.494 --> 00:58:42.994
I've secretly felt bad about only helping Dong Suk open her shop.

00:58:43.864 --> 00:58:45.104
You should open one, too.

00:58:48.774 --> 00:58:51.504
Actually, Father, instead of that,

00:58:52.474 --> 00:58:53.904
there's something else I'd like to ask.

00:58:54.344 --> 00:58:55.414
Sure.

00:58:56.144 --> 00:58:58.884
I'd like to go back to school.

00:58:59.884 --> 00:59:00.884
School?

00:59:01.654 --> 00:59:02.654
Yes.

00:59:02.954 --> 00:59:06.684
My credentials are what's keeping my husband from a council seat.

00:59:07.184 --> 00:59:09.324
I really want to study hard.

00:59:09.624 --> 00:59:11.624
I was a pretty good student, you know.

00:59:12.894 --> 00:59:14.294
I'm sure you were.

00:59:15.894 --> 00:59:18.094
I'll give you my full support.

00:59:20.204 --> 00:59:24.004
I know I can never be like Dr. Han Seong Mi.

00:59:24.734 --> 00:59:28.674
I refuse to just be a wife by his side, consumed with jealousy.

00:59:34.184 --> 00:59:37.084
(Taehan)

00:59:46.964 --> 00:59:48.164
Welcome, Doctor.

00:59:49.034 --> 00:59:50.994
My, what a grand welcome.

00:59:53.134 --> 00:59:56.104
This is the Vice President of Taehan Group.

00:59:57.274 --> 01:00:00.144
It's an honor, Doctor. I'm Hwangbo Hye Su.

01:00:00.274 --> 01:00:03.544
I hope I can pull my weight as the brand's model.

01:00:04.014 --> 01:00:05.184
We'll do our best to support you.

01:00:06.184 --> 01:00:08.984
This is Park Jun Hyeok and Gong Ju Ah.

01:00:13.454 --> 01:00:14.684
It's a pleasure to be working with you.

01:00:15.324 --> 01:00:18.024
- I'm a huge fan, Doctor. - Thank you.

01:00:20.494 --> 01:00:24.764
She's our head designer and the jewel of our Taehan Fashion.

01:00:28.674 --> 01:00:31.074
A pleasure to meet you, Ms. Gong Ju Ah.

01:00:33.174 --> 01:00:35.044
I look forward to working with you, Doctor.

01:00:48.524 --> 01:00:49.524
Here, Woo Jae.

01:00:50.694 --> 01:00:52.124
- Eun Bin. - Yes?

01:00:52.194 --> 01:00:54.224
I thought you said you'd start listening to your stepmom.

01:00:54.564 --> 01:00:57.564
If you keep following me like this, I bet your stepmom will be furious.

01:00:57.794 --> 01:01:00.034
Hey, if you're taking a break from studying,

01:01:00.034 --> 01:01:01.164
why not go on a trip with me instead?

01:01:01.234 --> 01:01:02.974
What's all this about getting a part-time job?

01:01:03.234 --> 01:01:05.644
I told you I'd earn money and support you.

01:01:05.704 --> 01:01:06.774
Don't be...

01:01:07.174 --> 01:01:10.344
- ridiculous. - Why? Am I wrong?

01:01:11.544 --> 01:01:13.484
I just want different experiences, that's all.

01:01:13.644 --> 01:01:17.614
Still, a barbecue joint? You should be tutoring or something.

01:01:17.954 --> 01:01:19.054
Tutor me.

01:01:19.524 --> 01:01:20.824
- It's time. - What?

01:01:20.824 --> 01:01:22.854
- I have to go. - Wait.

01:01:26.124 --> 01:01:27.124
Seriously.

01:01:36.004 --> 01:01:37.034
But...

01:01:37.704 --> 01:01:39.974
I'm not the only one doing well, am I, Sister?

01:01:41.104 --> 01:01:43.274
Veronica is doing very well, too.

01:01:50.354 --> 01:01:51.354
This...

01:01:52.554 --> 01:01:54.184
May I take it with me?

01:01:54.954 --> 01:01:56.794
Are you sure you'll be okay?

01:01:58.864 --> 01:02:00.624
This is all I have left.

01:02:02.234 --> 01:02:03.734
So I'm always thinking about it.

01:02:06.704 --> 01:02:08.234
I want to keep it with me now.

01:02:10.174 --> 01:02:13.304
I'll pray that He watches over you.

01:02:29.494 --> 01:02:31.654
(Damga Charcoal Grill, Onjeong Market)

01:02:31.724 --> 01:02:32.864
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

01:02:32.924 --> 01:02:34.164
Enjoy your meal.

01:02:34.494 --> 01:02:35.494
Thank you.

01:02:36.294 --> 01:02:37.294
Welcome.

01:02:42.274 --> 01:02:43.374
You're the one from...

01:02:44.074 --> 01:02:46.304
- Hello. - Hello.

01:02:46.844 --> 01:02:48.774
What? You know her?

01:02:49.914 --> 01:02:54.144
- You lost that pendant, right? - Yes. Do you happen to have it?

01:02:54.484 --> 01:02:55.614
Just a moment.

01:02:56.354 --> 01:02:57.384
Yes, here it is.

01:03:08.024 --> 01:03:09.034
Give that back, please.

01:03:11.394 --> 01:03:12.464
It's mine.

01:04:25.644 --> 01:04:28.444
(Recipe for Love)

01:04:28.504 --> 01:04:30.174
Ju Ah has a boyfriend?

01:04:30.244 --> 01:04:33.714
- I think he's a coworker, so watch. - Is it Jun Hyeok?

01:04:34.084 --> 01:04:35.084
What's this?

01:04:36.754 --> 01:04:40.354
Director Yang is someone who gets whatever he wants.

01:04:40.454 --> 01:04:43.924
- He's one of the best directors. - He sounds very impressive.

01:04:45.024 --> 01:04:48.164
Here's the golf coach. Looks like it's a couples' lesson.

01:04:48.224 --> 01:04:50.294
This is your chance. Go score some points with Seong Mi.

01:04:50.364 --> 01:04:52.164
Hey, how many times do I have to tell you?

01:04:52.234 --> 01:04:55.804
- Are you deaf? You fool! - With me...

01:04:56.074 --> 01:04:57.074
Go on, say it.

01:04:57.634 --> 01:04:59.944
With me...